description: Chasing Punjab Kings' challenging 214 for 5, Abhishek provided the quick start SRH needed, especially after Head departed for a first-ball duck. But Abhishek did not deviate from his attacking style of play and hit a blistering 66 off 28 balls, including 5 fours and 6 sixes. His good run has so far yielded 467 runs, incluing a season-highest 41 sixes.
title: 'Ye Team India ke darwaze tod rahe hain' - says Harbhajan about...

description: Bollywood star Akshay Kumar voted for the first time in the 2024 Lok Sabha election after obtaining Indian citizenship. He cast his vote early on Monday at a polling station in Mumbai's Juhu. Polling began at 7 am across 13 Lok Sabha constituencies in Maharashtra, including six in Mumbai. Akshay expressed his delight at participating in the electoral process.
title: Akshay Kumar casts vote for first time after Indian citizenship

description: Rajasthan Royals will face Royal Challengers Bengaluru in the Indian Premier League 2024 Eliminator on Wednesday, following a dramatic end to the league phase where Sunrisers Hyderabad pushed RR to third place. The Royals' subsequent match against Kolkata Knight Riders was washed out, cementing SRH's position based on net run rate.
title: Why ex-India cricketer feels RCB have upper hand over RR

description: A new Covid variant, KP.2 'FLiRT', a subvariant of Omicron, is causing an increase in Covid cases across states. The emergence coincides with Lok Sabha elections. Health officials report a mild symptom increase. KP.2 detected in Bengal (36 cases), Maharashtra (146 cases), and other states. State officials note low active cases and hospitalizations.
title: 'FLiRT': List of states affected by new Covid variant

description: A juvenile driver in Pune, driving a Porsche Taycan, was granted bail under the Juvenile Justice Act after causing a fatal crash that killed two motorcyclists. The court imposed conditions including 15 days of community service, a reflective essay, psychiatric counselling, and seeking help to quit drinking for the underage accused.
title: Minor crashes Porsche killing two, gets bail; asked to write essay
LS polls: In Ram's Ayodhya, a battle of prestige
Could Israel be behind crash of Iran President's helicopter?

description: PM Modi, speaking at a public rally in Angul, announced that if the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) wins in Odisha, they will appoint a chief minister from the local community. He criticized the current government, led by chief minister Naveen Patnaik of the Biju Janata Dal (BJD), and predicted the establishment of a "double-engine government" in Odisha for the first time.
title: BJP will make son or daughter of soil as CM: PM Modi

description: Mumbai to vote in 5th phase of Lok Sabha elections 2024. Salman Khan returns from Dubai to cast vote amidst security threats. Wears quirky manga print pants. Urges fans on social media to vote. Akshay Kumar votes after getting Indian citizenship in 2023. Emphasizes on voter turnout in India for development and strength.
title: Salman Khan returns home, just in time to vote in Lok Sabha elections

description: Thirty-six samples tested positive for the KP.2 variant, an Omicron offshoot, driving Covid cases. KP.2 replaces JN.1, found in 50% of samples, mainly from Kolkata. Belonging to the FLiRT group, KP.2 shows convergent evolution, causing mild symptoms.
title: 'FLiRT': West Bengal records 36 cases of newest Covid variant

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru fans have been hopeful for 17 seasons to win the Indian Premier League title. This season, RCB changed their name to Bengaluru and the catchline to "Hosa adhyaya," but their performance remained similar. However, a famous turnaround occurred with Faf du Plessis' team securing victories and making the playoffs.
title: Back from the brink: How RCB turned their fortunes around

description: Lai Ching-te was inaugurated as Taiwan's new president on Monday, stepping into a role fraught with challenges. He faces a deeply distrustful China, which views him as a "separatist," and a divided parliament with a determined opposition ready to contest his leadership. Previously serving as vice president under Tsai Ing-wen for the last four years, Lai took the oath of office in central Taipei.
title: New Taiwan Prez sworn, urges China to stop military intimidation

description: Bollywood actors urge fans to vote in Lok Sabha elections 2024. Akshay, Farhan, Zoya, and Janhvi spotted voting in Mumbai, expressing desire for India's development and strong future.
title: Lok Sabha elections 2024: Akshay Kumar casts vote

description: Chennai Super Kings legend MS Dhoni's 110-metre six against Royal Challengers Bengaluru was counterproductive, as he hit left-arm pacer Yash Dayal for a six in the first over. The ball was lost and replaced, causing Dhoni to miss the crucial second six and fulfill his promise of playing his last IPL match at Chepauk.
title: MS Dhoni swansong pushed back in playlist?

description: Virat Kohli and Chris Gayle had a lot of fun when the Jamaican giant walked into the Royal Challengers Bengaluru dressing room after the team's remarkable win over CSK to qualify for the IPL 2024 playoffs. An excited Kohli could be seen telling his former RCB teammate that he has now hit the most sixes in the ongoing IPL season.
title: Watch: 'I've hit most sixes' - Excited Virat tells Chris Gayle

description: On Saturday, Indian equities traded in two special sessions, from 9:15 a.m. to 10 a.m. (0345-0430 GMT) at a primary site and from 11:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. (0600-0700 GMT) at a disaster recovery site.
title: Why BSE Sensex, Nifty50 are closed for trading on May 20

description: Geoffrey Hinton, the 'godfather of AI,' warns about job loss due to AI and calls for universal basic income. He also highlights concerns about AI chatbots, extinction-level threats, and the military's use of AI. Additionally, he discusses the risks of large language models, autonomous decision-making, and the threat of AI takeover.
title: 'Very worried about AI taking lots of…,' says ‘Godfather of AI’

description: Google celebrated India's democratic franchise with a Doodle for the 2024 Lok Sabha Elections, featuring a voting symbol. The gesture emphasizes public participation. The fifth phase covers 49 constituencies across multiple states and union territories, with high-profile candidates. Google Doodles highlight significant cultural moments and historical milestones.
title: Google Doodle celebrates phase 5 of Lok Sabha Elections
‘Little Europe’ clings to last vestiges of its heritage

description: RCB qualified for the playoffs, finishing fourth on the points table after defeating CSK in their do-or-die match at the M Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bengaluru last Saturday. That was RCB's sixth consecutive win on the trot, after losing seven of their first eight matches in this edition, which is what makes their run special and iconic.
title: 'God's got a plan': Virat Kohli sums up RCB's rise from the ashes

description: After losing seven of their first eight matches, the Bengaluru team, led by Faf du Plessis and inspired by Orange Cap holder Virat Kohli (708 runs), won their next six matches on the trot to push CSK out of the race and finish in the top four on the leaderboard. They will now take on Rajasthan Royals in the Eliminator.
title: 'RCB se ummeed nahi thi because...' - How Virat & Co did it
